        "issued": "2026-04-25T14:32:00+00:00",
        "conclusion": ":\n1. Acute pulmonary emboli involving segmental and subsegmental branches of the right lower lobe pulmonary artery. The central pulmonary arteries are patent; this is a non-massive PE without evidence of right heart strain.\n2. Possible right lower lobe pulmonary infarct.\n3. Anticoagulation should be initiated. Recommend clinical correlation with hemodynamic status.",
